			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				as far as 1h vs 2h weapons goes, a 1h weapon and a shield can be a more effective way of fighting up to level 20.  At level 20 we get our damage cap off.  THAT is something to look forward to..imagine your slashing going from 20 dmg a hit to 40.  now since we dont get dual wield, when we hit level 20 you will be more effective using a 2handed weapon. if you need a list of some good weapons to look into here are some.<BR>
(by level 20 you should have at least 300pp saved up or have a way to get it)<BR>
<BR>
Blackened Iron Bastard Sword - 20 damage 47 delay and its magic - ive seen it normally go for 200pp which is a good price. you will be hitting hard with it but the delay sucks..group with a bard for some attack speed buffs and you will be a death machine.<BR>
<BR>
Tower Gaurd's Blade - 16dmg 36 delay magic - this sword does some hard hitting AND has good delay, its what i am currently using and is a great weapon. you can get it for about 200 - 300pp <BR>
<BR>
Runic Carver - 18 dmg 39 delay? (i think thats right i dont quite remember) this sword looks awesome! and its in pretty high demand too.  it usually goes for 400 - 600pp<BR>
<BR>
well there are a lot more weapons to look at just do go to the bank of a populated city and see what is being sold.  there are LOTS of ways to earn the money...some of which id rather not say due to the competition it would bring.  basically if you make some friends here and there you can get along a lot easier in norrath.  hope ive been of some help.<BR>
<BR>
Thuganator  -the human assault machine-
